<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1894</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vologda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-22"><hi rend="italic">May 22,
                                    1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 29, 5.20
                                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>192. Station agent Vologda received service message that Murman
                                Railroad cut on northern third by Finns. German submarines destroyed
                                Russian wireless station at Murman and sunk Russian freighters, and
                                several Norwegian fish boats in Murman waters.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_FDR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>